commit.message: Add ruby 3.2, remove some older ones
Remove mutex for finalizer, let ruby take care of it

attempt method now supports passing of previously

caught exception into the called block to let the handling behaviour
depend on it.

Also some smaller changes to make debugging on multiple ruby releases,
easier via all_images.
Ruby does it like you would expect for a while now

Add convenience method to create Tins::StringVersion

objects.

Pass previous exception to attempt block ...

... to allow reacting to it, logging it etc.

Add shebangs to examples

Some examples had executable bit set, but no shebang.
This is a strange configuration
and led Fedora buildsystem to issue a warning.
Fixed by adding the missing shebangs.
Use debug instead of byebug for development
Ignore more hidden files in the package
Remove some hidden/unneeded files from gem
